<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1/121: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-06T14:00:00-05:00">February
                                    6, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>47. Please cable any information available regarding the rumor current
                            here that the issuance of invitations for the International Sugar
                            Conference is being delayed on the ground that the United States will
                            probably not be able to support commitments that might be undertaken
                            regarding control of production and marketings of sugar.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>